"All that was revealed to me in 2-3-74." And I ask, "Who stole the secret?" and the answer is, "Valis." And I ask, "Who is Valis?" and at once comes the functional definition, "The Savior who combats the Deluder in the dialectic; the a priori wise horn of the dialectic is the entity that revealed the dialectic --and much more-- to me; that which I call Valis. So I had better be wary of dismissing Christianity so readily for Neo-Platonism: the dialectic implies a Savior; Valis' presence (epiphany) in my life implies --is in fact-- a Savior; and the sentence, "The secret stolen... " implies a Savior; and the AI voice itself implies a Savior, as well as other things it has said ("I will remain as your tutelary spirit"; "You have been adopted" etc.). And the dialectic implies an Adversary, as does the sentence, "He causes things to look different... " Etc. That leaves us with several possibilities: Zoroastrianism; Christianity; Gnosticism; Mani. And of these four, there is in actuality a blend; there are Zoroastrian elements in Christianity, Christian elements on Gnosticism, and Gnostic elements in Mani and Zoroastrian elements in Mani. So in a way these are variants on a single concept: the War Between the Sons of Darkness and the Sons of Light, as I put it in "VR." This is not found in Orphism, Platonism, Neo-Platonism, Buddhism, Brahmanism, Taoism. Then I see now what Christ is: the breaker of the Power of the Lie that caused us originally to Fall; he is the Revealer of the truth (reality), in contrast to this pseudo-world. Why, this is pure Gnostic Christianity! But I see; this is what was done for me in 2-3-74; Valis, then, is indeed the Cosmic Christ breaking the power of the Lie, the deluding spatiotemporal world. And this is an active mortal combat -- as I saw in the dialectic. But it didn't begin at the time of Acts; that was when the Cosmic Christ entered; but the Liar and the power of the Lie, his irreal domain, existed already (as Gnosticism teaches); so my ten volume meta novel is doing a salvific task; and VALIS is on the right track vis-a-vis Gnosticism. STIGMATA is particularly accurate. There is not only the domain of delusion (maya), there is also the Liar himself, creator of this illusory entrapping domain (Yaldabaoth). The following are involved: epistemology; choice; intellectual error; delusion and the deluding entity; the Revealer of the truth and a rectification of the intellectual choice (error). There is always the possibility that the builder of the maze (spatiotemporal

